DESCRIPTION

This is a library of some python functions useful for data analysis within the area of computational astrophysics.


AUTHOR

Marcel Zemp <marcelzemp@gmail.com>


OFFICIAL SOURCE

GitHub: https://github.com/mzemp/mzpylib


INSTALLATION

In order to call the python functions of the library, make sure that the installation path of the library (e.g. ~/libraries/ under your home directory) is included in the python search path by setting the following environment variable (e.g. in your .bashrc file):

export PYTHONPATH=~/libraries:$PYTHONPATH
